<aspnet_core_security_guide>
<title>ASP.NET CORE SECURITY TESTING</title>

<critical>ASP.NET Core is Microsoft's cross-platform web framework. Security vulnerabilities include authentication/authorization bypass, CSRF token issues, mass assignment, SQL injection through Entity Framework, and configuration exposure. Understanding ASP.NET Core's middleware pipeline and identity system is essential for security testing.</critical>

<scope>
- Authentication and Identity bypass
- Authorization policy circumvention
- Anti-forgery token (CSRF) bypass
- Model binding mass assignment
- Entity Framework Core injection
- Configuration and secrets exposure
- Razor Pages XSS
- SignalR security
</scope>

<methodology>
1. Identify ASP.NET Core version and configuration.
2. Test authentication endpoints and token handling.
3. Probe authorization policies for bypass.
4. Analyze model binding for mass assignment.
5. Test database queries for injection.
</methodology>

